      <hedline>
        <hl1>NORTH KOREAN ECONOMIC GROWTH</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Len, Samuel</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>South Korea's central bank says North Korea's economy expanded last year, ending decade of decline, helped by increased food production and international aid; north's economy grew 6.2 percent in 1999, after shrinking 1.1 percent in 1998 and 6.3 percent in 1997 (S)t</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Ending a decade of decline, North Korea's economy expanded last year, helped by increased food production and international aid, South Korea's central bank said. The north's economy grew 6.2 percent in 1999, after shrinking 1.1 percent in 1998 and 6.3 percent in 1997. Farming and fishing accounted for around a third of economic output. Last week the leaders of north and south held a historic summit meeting, and a relaxation of United States trade sanctions against the north quickly followed. The moves could lead to new business investment in the north.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len</p>
      </block>
